This paper deals with interpreting black box classifiers, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on deep networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses model compression, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new confidence measure based on dark knowledge, which is a concept in neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
